%% Diagram: Bypass toggle propagation + maintenance hold/drain (AD-032)
%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': {
  'primaryColor': '#eef2ff', 'primaryTextColor': '#1e293b',
  'primaryBorderColor': '#4f46e5', 'lineColor': '#94a3b8',
  'secondaryColor': '#ecfdf5', 'background': '#ffffff',
  'titleColor': '#1e293b', 'textColor': '#334155',
  'actorBkg': '#eef2ff', 'actorBorder': '#4f46e5',
  'noteBkgColor': '#fff7ed', 'noteBorderColor': '#f59e0b'
}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Admin
    participant API as CP API
    participant DB as node_control row
    participant Rec as NodeControlReconciler<br/>(fast lane)
    participant Dpstat as dpstat
    participant Map as node_control map
    participant Hot as XDP hot path
    participant Proc as apply dispatch

    Note over Admin,Hot: Emergency bypass — jumps the service-apply backlog
    Admin->>API: POST /node/bypass {enabled:true, reason}
    API->>DB: set bypass_enabled=true, activated_at, actor
    API->>API: record_event(node.bypass.enabled)
    API-->>Admin: 200 {desired:on, effective:off}
    loop every ~1s (independent of process_job)
        Rec->>DB: read desired
        alt bypass desired != asserted
            Rec->>Dpstat: set-bypass 1
            Dpstat->>Map: bpf_map_update_elem(bypass=1)
        end
    end
    Hot->>Map: per-packet read bypass
    Note over Hot: parsed IPv4 → redirect_out_bypass()<br/>skip pipeline, count bypass_counter,<br/>IPv6/malformed/fragment still drop

    Note over Admin,Proc: Maintenance — hold swaps, drain on exit
    Admin->>API: POST /node/maintenance {enabled:true}
    API->>DB: maintenance_enabled=true + audit
    Admin->>API: (config mutation) → M1 auto-enqueue
    API-->>Admin: 202 queued
    Proc->>DB: _maintenance_active? = true
    Note over Proc: leave SERVICE_UPDATE job queued<br/>(no mark_applying → no build → no flip)
    Admin->>API: POST /node/maintenance {enabled:false}
    API->>DB: maintenance_enabled=false + audit
    Rec->>DB: detect maintenance-clear edge
    Rec->>Proc: kick reconcile
    Note over Proc: drain queued backlog →<br/>build + single flip (latest wins, version-guarded)
